<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd"><html><head><meta content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1" http-equiv="content-type"><title>GAT Help</title><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Help.css"></head><body><h1>Stream link length</h1>

<p>
This tool can be used to measure the length of each link in a stream network. The user must specify the names of a <a href="StreamLinkID.html">stream link ID</a> raster image and <a href="FlowPointerD8.html">D8 pointer</a> image. The pointer image is used to traverse the stream network and should only be created using the <a href="FlowPointerD8.html">D8 algorithm</a>. Stream cells are designated in the stream link ID image as all non-zero, positive values. Background cells will be assigned the <b><i>NoData</b></i> value in the output image. The output raster is of a <i>float</i> data type and <i>continuous</i> data scale.</p>


